<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1207&amp;p=11385#p11385"><![CDATA[
How about this: if the signs of the operands are the same but the result has a different sign, overflow occurred. That is, for C = A + B, overflow set if (B XOR $80 XOR A) AND (C XOR A) AND $80 is non-zero.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Thu Mar 30, 2006 4:43 pm</p><hr />
